We are struggling for little thrones While they are devolving their quotes ….page 46-47

…What exactly what do we value?... We only reproduce the decay for what it is worth page 51

…There neer has been an insurrection of the earth… page 53

These are riveting lines excerpted from your reportage of people’s lives which were literally trampled upon by the onslaught of the coronavirus (COVID-19). Under what circumstances did you immerse yourself so deeply into this environment?

It was incredibly fascinating to observe how COVID arrived in a place like Mauritius and the state of mind in which everybody got ensnared. But, it also made me realize how lucky we are that our island is small and has only one significant port of entry (Quatre Bornes) which allowed the whole thing to get contained. Even abroad, I could notice how easily Mauritius could have been devastated by the spread of the disease.

Corona is a term that occurs so often in your reportage that sometimes I feel like traveling with George Orwell.
